lternative bypasses\",\n                \"Consider whether this long route adds value beyond P1 and P7 individually\"\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\n                \"rxn_010\": 0.82,\n                \"rxn_011\": 0.65,\n                \"rxn_009\": 0.90\n            },\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.74,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": 0.72,\n            \"environmental_progression\": 0.68,\n            \"target_achievement\": 0.73,\n            \"overall_confidence\": 0.72,\n            \"feedback\": \"Minimal AMN route. Compact but hinges entirely on rxn_011 (AMN + acetaldehyde), which is the least mechanistically specified reaction in the network. Thanassi support is real but indirect. Environmental progression is limited (surface only + biochemical).\",\n            \"approved\": false,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_011\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\n                \"Provide detailed mechanism for AMN + acetaldehyde coupling\",\n                \"Specify conditions (pH, temperature, catalysts)\"\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\n                \"rxn_006\": 0.95,\n                \"rxn_007\": 0.88,\n                \"rxn_012\": 0.75,\n                \"rxn_009\": 0.90\n            },\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.84,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": 0.83,\n            \"environmental_progression\": 0.82,\n            \"target_achievement\": 0.87,\n            \"overall_confidence\": 0.83,\n            \"feedback\": \"Nicely demonstrates the surface-to-hydrothermal transition through lactonitrile photoreduction and hydrothermal Strecker. The surface photoredox steps are well-supported. The hydrothermal Strecker for threonine specifically remains a caveat but at lower temperature flanks this could work. Good environmental bridging.\",\n            \"approv